In his remarks at the United Nations Security Council, Vice President Mike Pence emphasized the importance of peacekeeping and called for reforms to make peacekeeping operations more efficient and accountable. He also highlighted the threats posed by Russia, radical Islamic terrorism, Iran, and North Korea, and called on the UN to do more to confront these threats. Pence criticized the UN Human Rights Council for its biased treatment of Israel and called for reforms to its membership and practices. He also addressed the Rohingya crisis in Burma, urging the Security Council to take swift action to end the violence and provide assistance to the Rohingya people. Pence concluded his speech by calling on the UN to rededicate itself to its mission of maintaining international peace through reform and renewed courage.